payload/cx/  --  OLED CX-class demuxer-override payload
=======================================================

Profile: cx-armv7-gst114   (UNVERIFIED -- carried over from the shipping
dts_restore tool; no CX hardware was available to this project. See
../../README.md STATUS matrix.)

Drop the rebuilt LG GStreamer .so set HERE before packaging the .ipk:

    payload/cx/libgstisomp4.so
    payload/cx/libgstisomp4_1_8.so
    payload/cx/libgstmatroska.so
    payload/cx/libgstlibav.so
    payload/cx/libgstmpegtsdemux.so     (optional -- m2ts/BD; skipped if absent)

Where they come from
--------------------
These are the .so files from the repo root's gst/ directory (the shipping
dts_restore CX payload, built from LG's 1.14.4 GStreamer source with DTS demux
re-enabled + forced stereo-integer downmix):

    cp ../../../gst/*.so  ../dts-enabler-universal/payload/cx/

At enable time the JS service copies these to /var/lib/webosbrew/dtsenabler/cx/gst/
and bind-mounts them (read-only) over /usr/lib/gstreamer-1.0/, refreshes the
GStreamer registry, and bumps avdec_dca 0 -> 290 (+ [downmix]) in gstcool.conf.

WARNING: applying this mechanism on a NON-CX (e.g. webOS 25 / 1.24) TV would
bind-mount 1.14/armv7 libraries over 1.24 ones and break MKV/MP4 playback. The
service only ever selects this payload when the detector reports the
cx-armv7-gst114 profile (GStreamer 1.14.x); it refuses on any other profile.

Float-ABI caveat: MULTI-MODEL.md flags the CX "armv7 hard-float" claim as repo
lore, never measured on-device. The detector captures the loader + e_flags so
the real ABI can be confirmed before trusting this build.

These .so files are NOT committed (see ../../.gitignore). They are LGPL-2.1+;
ship the corresponding source offer with any distributed .ipk.
